<Layout title="Senior Homeowner: Step 04 of The Stairway | Stairway Mortgage" description="For homeowners 55 and older, the home often represents decades of equity — and a bridge to a secure, dignified retirement. This rung is about using th" canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/the-8-steps/senior-homeowner/">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)} />

  <header class="step-hero ">
    <div class="container-page step-hero__inner">
      <nav class="step-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/the-8-steps/">The 8 Steps</a> <span>/</span> <span>Senior Homeowner</span></nav>
      <span class="step-num" style="color:var(--color-blue)">04</span>
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--color-blue)">Phase 1 · Live in it · 55+ · The Bridge</span>
      <h1 class="display-xl step-hero__title">Senior Homeowner</h1>
      <p class="lede step-hero__lede">For homeowners 55 and older, the home often represents decades of equity — and a bridge to a secure, dignified retirement. This rung is about using that equity wisely to fund the years ahead while staying in the home you love.</p>
      <div class="step-progress mono">Step 04 of 08 · The Senior Planner</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="container-prose prose-editorial step-body" set:html={`<h2><b>What the Senior Homeowner step means</b></h2><p>Step four is the bridge. For seniors, home equity can supplement retirement income, fund care, or simply provide peace of mind — through reverse mortgages, downsizing strategies, or refinancing. The goal is security and choice in retirement.</p><h2><b>Who this step is for</b></h2><ul><li>Homeowners 55+ planning for retirement</li><li>Seniors with substantial equity and fixed income</li><li>Those wanting to age in place while accessing equity</li><li>Families planning a parent's financial security</li></ul><h2><b>The shift</b></h2><p>The shift is from accumulating to accessing — turning decades of equity into security and choice.</p><h2><b>How Stairway helps</b></h2><p>Reverse mortgages and senior financing are complex and deserve careful, honest counsel. We walk through the tradeoffs plainly — what it means for you and your heirs — so the decision is made with full clarity.</p><h2><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b></h2><h3><b>What does the Senior Homeowner step mean?</b></h3><p>Step four is the bridge. For seniors, home equity can supplement retirement income, fund care, or simply provide peace of mind — through reverse mortgages, downsizing strategies, or refinancing. The goal is security and choice in retirement.</p><h3><b>Who is the Senior Homeowner step for?</b></h3><p>It's for homeowners 55+ planning for retirement, and others making this transition. The shift is from accumulating to accessing — turning decades of equity into security and choice.</p><h3><b>How do I move to the next step?</b></h3><p>The next rung is First-Time Investor — From Consumer to Owner. We can help you take the next step when you're ready.</p>`} />

  <div class="container-prose"><div class="step-cta-card ">
    <h2 class="display-md">Ready for this step?</h2>
    <p class="lede">Reverse mortgages and senior financing are complex and deserve careful, honest counsel. We walk through the tradeoffs pl</p>
    <a href="/reverse-mortgage-journey/" class="btn btn-blue btn-arrow">Explore Reverse Mortgage</a>
  </div></div>

